00:59:40,910 --> 00:59:42,412
Why weren't you at school?

778
00:59:42,495 --> 00:59:45,331
I was a little sick. Look at me,
don't you think I lost weight?

779
00:59:45,915 --> 00:59:48,084
Yes, it looks like you did.
Are you okay now?

780
00:59:48,167 --> 00:59:50,962
Yeah, I'm fine. Oh! How was your birthday?

781
00:59:51,045 --> 00:59:52,589
I'm sorry I couldn't contact you.

782
00:59:52,672 --> 00:59:54,299
You don't need to be sorry.

783
00:59:54,799 --> 00:59:58,303
Uh, did you talk to Sol already?
She seemed pretty worried about you.

784
00:59:59,012 --> 01:00:02,265
Oh, just look at the weather today,
it's so nice!

785
01:00:02,348 --> 01:00:04,392
It's the perfect spring weather.

786
01:00:04,475 --> 01:00:05,685
Yeah, it is.

787
01:00:07,228 --> 01:00:09,188
I don't want to work
on assignments.

788
01:00:09,272 --> 01:00:11,566
Oh, hey, you look so pretty, Na-bi.

789
01:00:11,649 --> 01:00:13,026
-Are you here to work?
-Oh, yeah. So pretty.

790
01:00:13,109 --> 01:00:15,486
-We're just having a short meeting.
-They look so pretty.

791
01:00:15,570 --> 01:00:17,572
Yeah,
the dress looks good on her.

792
01:00:17,655 --> 01:00:18,781
Okay.

793
01:00:20,617 --> 01:00:21,659
Go on.

794
01:00:32,712 --> 01:00:34,756
And me? What about me?

795
01:00:34,839 --> 01:00:37,050
It's been a while
since we saw you, Ji-wan.

796
01:00:37,133 --> 01:00:38,593
Why did you suddenly go off the grid?

797
01:00:38,676 --> 01:00:40,261
Well, I was a bit sick.

798
01:00:42,472 --> 01:00:45,141
How does a fit girl like you
suddenly get sick?

799
01:00:45,725 --> 01:00:47,685
I know.
Ji-wan is built like a rock.

800
01:00:47,769 --> 01:00:49,228
What were you sick with, Ji-wan?

801
01:00:49,812 --> 01:00:53,107
All right. Well, Jae-eon can't come
with us since he has plans this weekend.

802
01:00:53,191 --> 01:00:54,692
Anyone else who can't come?

803
01:00:55,193 --> 01:00:56,736
Hey, Na-bi.

804
01:00:56,819 --> 01:00:59,530
We're going to check out the venue
for our workshop. Want to come with us?

805
01:01:00,573 --> 01:01:01,658
Uh…

806
01:01:06,579 --> 01:01:08,456
Sorry, I also have plans.

807
01:01:09,457 --> 01:01:12,669
Right. If you have plans,
then I guess not.

808
01:01:14,128 --> 01:01:15,046
Hmm.

809
01:01:29,310 --> 01:01:32,689
Did you see Na-bi and Jae-eon?
It looks like they're dating, right?

810
01:01:32,772 --> 01:01:35,024
I really thought Na-bi had a crush on me.

811
01:01:35,525 --> 01:01:37,402
Really, Jin-su?
You're still on about that?

812
01:01:37,485 --> 01:01:38,861
You gotta give up on her.

813
01:01:38,945 --> 01:01:41,489
Hey, you guys free today?
Want to go out for drinks?

814
01:01:41,572 --> 01:01:43,032
-Hmm.
-I have plans.

815
01:01:43,116 --> 01:01:44,283
Jerk.

816
01:01:44,784 --> 01:01:47,245
Yeah, me too. I also have plans.

817
01:01:59,298 --> 01:02:01,551
Not you again.

818
01:02:10,309 --> 01:02:11,519
What are you doing here?

819
01:02:11,602 --> 01:02:14,397
Na-bi, I'm absolutely
heartbroken right now.

820
01:02:14,480 --> 01:02:16,232
And I know you're in a lot of pain after--

821
01:02:16,315 --> 01:02:17,775
What are you talking about?

822
01:02:20,695 --> 01:02:21,821
I heard the rumors.

823
01:02:21,904 --> 01:02:23,781
A lot of my students
attend your school too.

824
01:02:23,865 --> 01:02:26,826
I keep hearing rumors about you,
even if I try hard not to.

825
01:02:26,909 --> 01:02:27,869
What do you mean?

826
01:02:29,203 --> 01:02:30,747
-What rumors?
-I heard you're seeing

827
01:02:30,830 --> 01:02:34,459
some jerk named Park Jae-eon or something.

828
01:02:35,251 --> 01:02:37,336
I heard that he sleeps
with everybody he meets.

829
01:02:37,420 --> 01:02:39,839
I was so shocked when I heard
that you were seeing him.

830
01:02:44,719 --> 01:02:47,263
I don't like hearing
about my ex's new dating life.

831
01:02:49,682 --> 01:02:50,808
Let go of me.

832
01:02:51,851 --> 01:02:54,228
You're really giving me advice?
Who do you think you are?

833
01:02:54,312 --> 01:02:57,148
What? So it's true?
You're seeing that bastard?

834
01:02:57,231 --> 01:02:59,108
Who are you to call him a bastard, huh?

835
01:02:59,192 --> 01:03:00,735
-Yu Na-bi!
-What?

836
01:03:04,113 --> 01:03:06,365
Listen, you're not that kind of girl, huh!

837
01:03:06,449 --> 01:03:08,117
You must've been lonely after we broke up.

838
01:03:08,201 --> 01:03:10,787
But still, seeing a guy like that?
There are much better guys out there.

839
01:03:10,870 --> 01:03:12,371
-You can be--
-Shut up and get lost.

840
01:03:19,253 --> 01:03:20,755
Hey. Hey, Na-bi…

841
01:03:23,591 --> 01:03:27,303
LAUNDRY

842
01:03:38,147 --> 01:03:40,274
Asshole. Who does he think he is?

843
01:04:04,131 --> 01:04:07,009
I feel like I'm doing
something wrong, but I don't know what.

844
01:04:08,261 --> 01:04:10,137
Oh, hey,
don't you know any hot girls?

845
01:04:10,847 --> 01:04:13,099
Go ask Jae-eon, I'm sure he knows a lot.

846
01:04:14,100 --> 01:04:15,059
Park Jae-eon?

847
01:04:15,852 --> 01:04:18,271
To be honest,
I don't really feel comfortable with him.

848
01:04:19,021 --> 01:04:21,607
Why? Did something happen between you two?

849
01:04:21,691 --> 01:04:24,819
Don't you feel like he's been showing off
his popularity too much?

850
01:04:24,902 --> 01:04:27,280
When I asked him
to introduce me to a hot girl,

851
01:04:27,363 --> 01:04:31,075
he said something about feeling guilty
towards her. It totally pissed me off.

852
01:04:31,659 --> 01:04:34,495
Seriously?
Jae-eon really said all that to you?

853
01:04:34,579 --> 01:04:36,205
He did, I'm telling you.

854
01:04:36,289 --> 01:04:38,124
He's so rude just because he's popular.

855
01:04:38,207 --> 01:04:40,084
We don't really think of him
as a real friend.

856
01:04:40,167 --> 01:04:42,336
And the others
don't consider him a friend, either.

857
01:04:42,420 --> 01:04:45,339
They just keep him close
since he's so good-looking.

858
01:04:46,966 --> 01:04:48,634
His target is Yu Na-bi these days.

859
01:04:49,302 --> 01:04:50,887
They seem to be getting close.

860
01:04:50,970 --> 01:04:52,471
I could totally tell.

861
01:04:52,555 --> 01:04:55,474
Yeah, I heard about that rumor.

862
01:04:55,558 --> 01:04:57,351
So the rumors
are spreading already.

863
01:04:57,435 --> 01:04:59,395
In any case, Jae-eon has nothing to lose.

864
01:04:59,478 --> 01:05:00,605
He must be very proud.

865
01:05:01,731 --> 01:05:04,901
I didn't think Na-bi would be like that.
She must be pretty open-minded--

866
01:05:04,984 --> 01:05:06,777
Open-minded?

867
01:05:06,861 --> 01:05:09,447
Come on. That's just a nice way to put it.

868
01:05:10,072 --> 01:05:13,492
Listen to me, you really
can't judge a book by its cover.

869
01:05:14,410 --> 01:05:16,203
Well, I should get going now.

870
01:05:16,787 --> 01:05:18,289
Okay. I'll go with you.

871
01:05:23,544 --> 01:05:24,754
Yu Na-bi?

872
01:05:27,590 --> 01:05:29,967
Uh… Hello there, Professor.

873
01:05:32,887 --> 01:05:34,138
Is this piece for the exhibit?

874
01:05:34,722 --> 01:05:38,017
Uh… Yeah, I'm thinking of handing
this sculpture in.

875
01:05:46,525 --> 01:05:48,152
Is something troubling you?

876
01:05:48,235 --> 01:05:49,737
Because it's in pretty bad shape.

877
01:05:50,446 --> 01:05:51,781
Right hook.

878
01:05:53,240 --> 01:05:57,203
But still, if you focus well
and keep working on it,

879
01:05:58,037 --> 01:05:59,497
it could turn out to be a decent piece.

880
01:05:59,580 --> 01:06:02,124
Okay. I'll work harder on it.

881
01:06:18,099 --> 01:06:19,517
Listen to me, Na-bi.

882
01:06:19,600 --> 01:06:22,520
It's so easy for people
to gossip about others

883
01:06:22,603 --> 01:06:24,855
and criticize them
for the choices they make.

884
01:06:24,939 --> 01:06:27,900
It's especially worse in Korea,
since it's a small country.

885
01:06:29,193 --> 01:06:32,655
That's why when you're young,
you should be careful about what you do.

886
01:06:33,656 --> 01:06:36,075
You might think that all
your reckless behavior can be forgiven

887
01:06:36,158 --> 01:06:37,034
because you're young.

888
01:06:40,204 --> 01:06:42,832
However, from what I experienced,
that's not the case.

889
01:06:43,416 --> 01:06:44,625
There are consequences.

890
01:06:44,709 --> 01:06:47,878
You'll get hit with the aftermath
at any crucial moment.

891
01:06:47,962 --> 01:06:49,422
Left hook.

892
01:06:49,505 --> 01:06:52,258
No one else will take responsibility
for your life.

893
01:06:52,341 --> 01:06:55,886
So keep your head on straight.
You're graduating soon, you know.

894
01:06:55,970 --> 01:06:58,389
Nowadays, everyone finds a job
before they graduate.

895
01:06:59,015 --> 01:07:00,725
And there's the uppercut.

896
01:07:01,559 --> 01:07:02,643
Right.

897
01:07:03,436 --> 01:07:04,895
I know how you feel, Na-bi.

898
01:07:04,979 --> 01:07:08,190
So I'm giving you advice since
I care about you. Keep that in mind.

899
01:07:08,858 --> 01:07:09,692
Yes.

900
01:07:10,776 --> 01:07:13,904
-Focus on your work.
-I will, Professor.

901
01:07:20,786 --> 01:07:21,996
K.O.

902
01:07:35,301 --> 01:07:36,802
It feels like,

903
01:07:36,886 --> 01:07:40,389
the entire universe is telling me
to end it with Jae-eon once and for all.

904
01:07:41,223 --> 01:07:42,266
Na-bi.

905
01:07:44,935 --> 01:07:48,064
Are you okay?
You could've fallen in the trash.

906
01:07:48,939 --> 01:07:51,233
Yeah. Oh, I'm okay.

907
01:07:51,942 --> 01:07:54,111
Uh, I'm actually glad you're here.

908
01:07:54,195 --> 01:07:57,198
I was wondering,
if you and I could meet after school.

909
01:07:59,283 --> 01:08:02,369
Well, I… like the fact
that you're asking first,

910
01:08:02,453 --> 01:08:05,164
but I have a lot of work today,
so I'll be a bit tired.

911
01:08:06,665 --> 01:08:09,335
What are you saying?
I'm not talking about that.

912
01:08:11,587 --> 01:08:13,672
I just want us to talk, that's all.

913
01:08:14,840 --> 01:08:17,593
All right, then.
Can we meet later tonight?

914
01:08:17,676 --> 01:08:18,803
Yeah, it's fine.

915
01:08:20,054 --> 01:08:21,555
I'll call you when I'm done with work.

916
01:08:23,057 --> 01:08:24,058
Hmm.

917
01:08:35,778 --> 01:08:37,613
Let's send it
to the professor tomorrow.

918
01:08:37,696 --> 01:08:38,531
Okay.

919
01:08:38,614 --> 01:08:40,658
She won't read it
until tomorrow anyway.

920
01:08:49,041 --> 01:08:50,668
-Aren't you leaving yet?
-What?

921
01:08:51,210 --> 01:08:56,090
Oh, well… I'll just finish reading
the paper I was looking at earlier.

922
01:08:58,050 --> 01:08:59,093
Where is it?

923
01:08:59,176 --> 01:09:02,138
All right. Um, I'll go ahead, then.

924
01:09:02,721 --> 01:09:04,223
Yeah, okay. Bye.

925
01:09:06,392 --> 01:09:07,476
I thought about it,

926
01:09:07,560 --> 01:09:10,229
and I guess I must have lost it
after breaking up with that jerk.

927
01:09:10,312 --> 01:09:12,148
I don't know why I'm doing this

928
01:09:12,231 --> 01:09:14,150
with someone like you.

929
01:09:17,486 --> 01:09:18,821
What do you mean by that?

930
01:09:21,407 --> 01:09:23,993
I want to focus on my work
and education from now on.

931
01:09:26,620 --> 01:09:28,497
This is a very important time for me.

932
01:09:30,291 --> 01:09:32,209
I guess I'm talking too much, aren't I?

933
01:09:32,918 --> 01:09:35,296
Mm-hm. Aren't you going overboard?

934
01:09:35,379 --> 01:09:36,881
We're not even going out.

935
01:09:41,385 --> 01:09:42,595
We should end it, Jae-eon.

936
01:09:48,184 --> 01:09:50,644
Does that sound like I wanna cut ties?

937
01:09:54,982 --> 01:09:57,693
Whether I say this or whether I say that,

938
01:09:57,776 --> 01:10:00,988
I know that Jae-eon won't even bat an eye.

939
01:10:06,994 --> 01:10:09,246
He's always so calm
and I'm always so anxious.

940
01:10:09,330 --> 01:10:12,833
I mean, my ex cheated on me,
a guy who liked me rejected me,

941
01:10:12,917 --> 01:10:16,545
and rumors are spreading around
about me casually dating a guy I like.

942
01:10:17,046 --> 01:10:18,130
Whoa!

943
01:10:19,590 --> 01:10:22,134
It sounds even worse
when I put it all together.

944
01:10:30,517 --> 01:10:32,478
We should end it.

945
01:10:33,354 --> 01:10:34,855
That's all I have to say.

946
01:10:52,665 --> 01:10:53,958
I need to talk to you, Ji-wan.

947
01:10:54,041 --> 01:10:55,668
What else is there to talk about?

948
01:10:57,294 --> 01:11:00,506
To be honest, I don't even get
why you're so upset.

949
01:11:02,383 --> 01:11:03,842
You didn't need to ghost me like that.

950
01:11:08,555 --> 01:11:10,307
I said I'll see you at your house.

951
01:11:12,059 --> 01:11:14,520
Uh, well, I thought
you'd take a long time.

952
01:11:15,521 --> 01:11:18,941
I thought I'd finish by 10:00 p.m.,
but it's taking longer than expected.

953
01:11:19,566 --> 01:11:20,567
Right.

954
01:11:22,444 --> 01:11:23,487
I see.

955
01:11:23,570 --> 01:11:27,199
I ran thousands of simulations
of this moment inside my head.

956
01:11:28,325 --> 01:11:29,702
You look pretty serious.

957
01:11:32,162 --> 01:11:33,247
What did you want to say?

958
01:11:33,747 --> 01:11:35,457
But the moment
I looked into his eyes…

959
01:11:37,584 --> 01:11:39,211
my mind went blank.

960
01:11:39,920 --> 01:11:41,046
Well…

961
01:11:43,632 --> 01:11:45,926
My ex-boyfriend
came to my house the other night.

962
01:11:46,010 --> 01:11:48,846
It looks like he heard rumors
about us from his students.

963
01:11:50,973 --> 01:11:52,891
He said I should just date him instead.

964
01:11:55,853 --> 01:11:57,062
And what did you tell him?

965
01:11:58,022 --> 01:11:59,815
I said his opinion doesn't matter to me.

966
01:12:01,066 --> 01:12:02,067
Really?

967
01:12:02,151 --> 01:12:05,029
"Really?" Is that it?

968
01:12:10,159 --> 01:12:11,869
Is that what you wanted to say?

969
01:12:16,790 --> 01:12:19,168
Is there another girl
you're seeing other than me?

970
01:12:19,251 --> 01:12:20,669
What's wrong with me?

971
01:12:21,170 --> 01:12:23,714
Why am I asking this
when I'm about to end everything?

972
01:12:28,802 --> 01:12:29,928
There's none.

973
01:12:31,347 --> 01:12:32,264
Really?

974
01:12:48,280 --> 01:12:49,573
Excuse me.

975
01:12:50,157 --> 01:12:52,785
Are you, uh…
Are you Park Jae-eon, by any chance?

976
01:12:53,827 --> 01:12:54,661
Yeah.

977
01:12:56,914 --> 01:12:58,165
So it's you, huh?

978
01:13:01,418 --> 01:13:04,338
You fucking bastard!

979
01:13:05,005 --> 01:13:06,924
Sir, stop it! Please, calm down!

980
01:13:07,007 --> 01:13:09,051
-What are you doing?
-Move.

981
01:13:09,134 --> 01:13:10,552
-Are you crazy?
-Move it!

982
01:13:10,636 --> 01:13:12,554
-Why are you doing this?
-Get out of the way!

983
01:13:15,307 --> 01:13:16,350
Na-bi!

984
01:14:11,822 --> 01:14:14,241
Jae-eon has never been mine
to begin with.

985
01:14:14,324 --> 01:14:15,784
But it feels like I've lost him.

986
01:14:15,868 --> 01:14:18,537
How could Na-bi
date a guy like Jae-eon?

987
01:14:18,620 --> 01:14:20,664
-My girlfriend?
-Call me.

988
01:14:20,747 --> 01:14:22,207
Even if it isn't anything special.

989
01:14:22,291 --> 01:14:25,252
My entire house is filled
with traces of Jae-eon.

990
01:14:25,335 --> 01:14:26,170
That jerk.

991
01:14:26,837 --> 01:14:28,380
I guess it worked, then.

992
01:14:28,464 --> 01:14:30,048
Are you still avoiding me?

993
01:14:30,132 --> 01:14:32,468
It's just that,
we didn't get to finish talking.

994
01:14:32,551 --> 01:14:35,762
That's how it's always been with us.
We act like nothing happened.

995
01:14:35,846 --> 01:14:37,556
I just got it. I thought of you.

996
01:14:37,639 --> 01:14:39,600
-This is for me?
-Mm-hm.

997
01:14:39,683 --> 01:14:41,393
'Cause I was jealous. Good luck today.

998
01:14:41,477 --> 01:14:43,896
Who would like to volunteer
to assist Na-bi? Raise your hand.

999
01:14:43,979 --> 01:14:46,064
We could have a lot of fun. And I think
they're amazing and interesting.

1000
01:14:46,148 --> 01:14:48,025
Hello, Seol-a. I'm going there.

1001
01:14:48,108 --> 01:14:50,402
How can he not even call once?

1002
01:14:50,486 --> 01:14:51,945
I miss him.
